```json
{
"application": "Spack",
"details": {
"scheduler": "Slurm",
"scheduler_module": "slurm",
"slurm_account": "sdsc",
"slurm_partition": "hotel",
"slurm_nodes": 1,
"slurm_tasks_per_node": 1,
"slurm_cpus_per_task": 10,
"slurm_memory": "93G",
"slurm_gpus": 1,
"slurm_time": "00:30:00",
"spack_version": "0.17.3",
"spack_instance_name": "gpu",
"spack_instance_dir": "${HOME}/cm/shared/apps/spack/${SPACK_VERSION}/${SPACK_INSTANCE_NAME}",
"spack_package": "hdf5@1.10.7",
"spack_compiler": "gcc@10.2.0",
"spack_variants": "+cxx +fortran +hl ~ipo +java +mpi +shared ~szip ~threadsafe +tools",
"spack_dependencies": "^intel-mpi@2019.10.317/$(spack find --format '{hash:7}' intel-mpi@2019.10.317 % ${SPACK_COMPILER})",
"spack_spec": "${SPACK_PACKAGE} % ${SPACK_COMPILER} ${SPACK_VARIANTS} ${SPACK_DEPENDENCIES}",
"system_name": "expanse",
"dependencies": [
"parmetis@4.0.3.sh"
]
}
}
```

This script is using the Spack package manager to install the HDF5 library version 1.10.7 compiled with GCC 10.2.0.  It is running on a Slurm cluster, utilizing various resources including 10 CPUs, 93GB of memory, 1 GPU, and a runtime of 30 minutes.  The script also specifies the dependencies required for installing HDF5, including Intel MPI 2019.10.317, and then runs a subsequent script for `parmetis@4.0.3` after the installation completes.
